1
00:00:22,464 --> 00:00:26,432
♪Should we forget yesterday's sorrows♪

2
00:00:26,432 --> 00:00:29,728
♪And the dazed confusion♪

3
00:00:30,976 --> 00:00:33,681
♪Should we let go of♪

4
00:00:33,681 --> 00:00:35,904
♪The stubborn madness♪

5
00:00:35,904 --> 00:00:39,072
♪And naive recklessness now♪

6
00:00:40,192 --> 00:00:43,840
♪Those years, those faces♪

7
00:00:44,992 --> 00:00:48,763
♪Those old scars we can't erase♪

8
00:00:49,824 --> 00:00:52,460
♪Tears streaming, facing the light♪

9
00:00:53,152 --> 00:00:57,594
♪Piercing the sorrow within♪

10
00:01:08,716 --> 00:01:12,736
♪The road ahead's long,
stumbling all the way♪

11
00:01:13,536 --> 00:01:18,076
♪The wounds we've borne
are medals hidden within♪

12
00:01:18,336 --> 00:01:22,391
♪Standing alone on an open plain♪

13
00:01:23,168 --> 00:01:26,851
♪We gaze at the stars♪

14
00:01:31,228 --> 00:01:34,816
=The Dream Maker=

15
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,715
=Episode 18=

16
00:01:50,066 --> 00:01:50,706
Mr. Lin.

17
00:01:51,986 --> 00:01:52,545
Please sit.

18
00:01:53,506 --> 00:01:54,105
Okay.

19
00:02:05,305 --> 00:02:06,346
Yan.

20
00:02:08,506 --> 00:02:10,705
There was a beauty...

21
00:02:13,105 --> 00:02:13,985
I forgot it.

22
00:02:15,186 --> 00:02:15,865
I...

23
00:02:16,665 --> 00:02:19,066
I look at the beauty while...

24
00:02:19,746 --> 00:02:20,246
No.

25
00:02:20,425 --> 00:02:22,346
I look at you...

26
00:02:34,186 --> 00:02:34,906
Mr. Lin.

27
00:02:35,786 --> 00:02:37,145
I couldn't hear you clearly.

28
00:02:37,466 --> 00:02:38,186
It's fine.

29
00:02:38,946 --> 00:02:40,306
I'll sit closer. Please go ahead.

30
00:02:42,985 --> 00:02:43,626
I...

31
00:02:45,385 --> 00:02:46,385
I look at you.

32
00:02:47,145 --> 00:02:48,066
And you look at me.

33
00:02:48,946 --> 00:02:49,705
I'm looking at you.

34
00:02:49,865 --> 00:02:51,145
No, don't look at me.

35
00:02:55,346 --> 00:02:56,506
Then I won't look at you.

36
00:03:06,865 --> 00:03:07,864
Look at the clouds.

37
00:03:10,265 --> 00:03:10,865
Clouds?

38
00:03:14,506 --> 00:03:15,066
Y...

39
00:03:17,145 --> 00:03:18,985
There's a bridge in the sky.

40
00:03:20,705 --> 00:03:21,205
You...

41
00:03:21,906 --> 00:03:23,066
Never mind about any bridge.

42
00:03:36,865 --> 00:03:38,265
Were you building a wall here?

43
00:03:44,825 --> 00:03:47,306
Your mortar mix is too thin.

44
00:03:49,026 --> 00:03:50,946
The cement-to-sand ratio
should be one to two.

45
00:03:51,306 --> 00:03:53,626
Too much cement
means you need more water.

46
00:03:53,626 --> 00:03:54,665
So it's too much water.

47
00:03:55,026 --> 00:03:55,985
With too much water,

48
00:03:56,145 --> 00:03:57,906
it'll definitely crack later.

49
00:03:58,626 --> 00:03:59,865
And, after mixing it,

50
00:03:59,906 --> 00:04:02,346
you must use it within three hours.

51
00:04:02,506 --> 00:04:03,746
Otherwise, it loses adhesion.

52
00:04:04,226 --> 00:04:05,585
Depending on the season,

53
00:04:05,906 --> 00:04:07,385
the time limits vary.

54
00:04:07,626 --> 00:04:10,545
In summer, it gets even shorter.

55
00:04:12,346 --> 00:04:13,066
Furthermore,

56
00:04:15,545 --> 00:04:17,785
this wall isn't straight.

57
00:04:18,785 --> 00:04:19,746
Skipped the guideline?

58
00:04:20,746 --> 00:04:21,426
Guideline?

59
00:04:23,585 --> 00:04:24,866
You have the tools right here.

60
00:04:25,705 --> 00:04:26,426
Why not use them?

61
00:04:26,525 --> 00:04:27,866
Come on, let me show you.

62
00:04:28,585 --> 00:04:30,785
Tie the line to this brick.

63
00:04:31,746 --> 00:04:33,186
So this is how it's used.

64
00:04:33,546 --> 00:04:34,046
Okay.

65
00:04:34,426 --> 00:04:35,025
Watch.

66
00:04:35,306 --> 00:04:38,306
Find a reference point here
for the wall.

67
00:04:39,066 --> 00:04:40,025
Lift it up.

68
00:04:40,385 --> 00:04:40,885
See?

69
00:04:41,225 --> 00:04:42,946
Let it hang for positioning.

70
00:04:43,705 --> 00:04:46,225
Now mark it with an ink line.

71
00:04:46,905 --> 00:04:48,746
You have an ink pot but don't use it.

72
00:04:49,986 --> 00:04:50,946
I don't know how.

73
00:04:54,905 --> 00:04:57,145
Find the point we marked.

74
00:04:57,225 --> 00:04:57,746
Snap it.

75
00:04:58,306 --> 00:04:58,806
Okay.

76
00:05:02,705 --> 00:05:04,785
Have you read
the latest issue of New City Life?

77
00:05:05,306 --> 00:05:06,506
An article on page three

78
00:05:06,506 --> 00:05:08,145
is quite interesting.
You should read it.

79
00:05:08,585 --> 00:05:10,866
It's a debate on
drinking milk in the morning

80
00:05:10,866 --> 00:05:13,306
or night for better health.

81
00:05:13,345 --> 00:05:14,186
Experts...

82
00:05:14,225 --> 00:05:15,905
They should've invited

83
00:05:15,905 --> 00:05:18,006
people at our level
for this debate, right?

84
00:05:18,025 --> 00:05:19,825
Does timing really matter that much?

85
00:05:20,746 --> 00:05:21,585
Drink it warm.

86
00:05:21,905 --> 00:05:23,825
Cold milk gives you
stomachaches anytime.

87
00:05:23,825 --> 00:05:25,225
Medical experts mentioned...

88
00:05:25,225 --> 00:05:26,705
Where does it say that?

89
00:05:27,145 --> 00:05:28,345
Can't you read these?

90
00:05:29,186 --> 00:05:30,426
The author is Rambler.

91
00:05:30,465 --> 00:05:32,145
On such a trivial topic? Rambler?

92
00:05:32,546 --> 00:05:33,306
Ridiculous.

93
00:05:34,225 --> 00:05:35,946
These newspapers are doomed.

94
00:05:35,946 --> 00:05:36,465
Wear glasses.

95
00:05:36,506 --> 00:05:37,106
You!

96
00:05:37,465 --> 00:05:38,825
Xie, what are you talking about?

97
00:05:39,225 --> 00:05:40,385
- What do you mean?
- I'm speaking the truth.

98
00:05:40,986 --> 00:05:41,825
They won't be doomed.

99
00:05:41,825 --> 00:05:43,225
Rambler is Du Tao.

100
00:05:43,866 --> 00:05:44,585
I knew it.

101
00:05:45,265 --> 00:05:46,626
Work has no hierarchy.

102
00:05:46,946 --> 00:05:48,145
National affairs matter.

103
00:05:48,186 --> 00:05:49,848
Knowing when to drink milk matters too.

104
00:05:50,265 --> 00:05:52,066
These health tips

105
00:05:52,145 --> 00:05:53,345
matter for us.

106
00:05:53,785 --> 00:05:54,825
- Right.
- Don't you drink milk?

107
00:05:55,426 --> 00:05:57,585
- Yes, we all drink milk.
- We do.

108
00:05:57,746 --> 00:05:58,905
Ms. Li is right.

109
00:05:58,946 --> 00:05:59,585
Drink it warm.

110
00:05:59,585 --> 00:06:00,465
Milk is excellent.

111
00:06:00,465 --> 00:06:02,825
Full of protein and nutrients.

112
00:06:04,506 --> 00:06:05,905
Hello, Yuehai Town Government.

113
00:06:16,785 --> 00:06:17,465
Understood.

114
00:06:19,746 --> 00:06:21,626
Mr. Zheng, the Meteorological Bureau

115
00:06:21,986 --> 00:06:24,145
said a typhoon is expected
to attack Yuehai soon.

116
00:06:24,465 --> 00:06:26,106
The expected wind force is 8 to 11.

117
00:06:30,506 --> 00:06:32,825
We still need a level line now.

118
00:06:33,986 --> 00:06:34,626
Here.

119
00:06:35,186 --> 00:06:35,785
Look.

120
00:06:36,066 --> 00:06:37,666
First, find a fixed point here.

121
00:06:39,145 --> 00:06:41,106
Must secure it firmly.

122
00:06:41,746 --> 00:06:42,265
Okay.

123
00:06:46,002 --> 00:06:48,274
(Malted Milk Powder)

124
00:06:50,345 --> 00:06:50,866
Okay.

125
00:06:51,225 --> 00:06:54,225
Then pull along this line.

126
00:07:05,666 --> 00:07:06,746
Find a whole brick.

127
00:07:12,225 --> 00:07:12,725
Alright.

128
00:07:13,145 --> 00:07:13,785
See?

129
00:07:14,385 --> 00:07:17,546
Now we have
both a level line and a plumb line,

130
00:07:18,106 --> 00:07:20,866
so we can build
a straight and sturdy wall.

131
00:07:23,066 --> 00:07:23,705
Thirsty?

132
00:07:41,265 --> 00:07:41,946
Thanks.

133
00:07:43,025 --> 00:07:43,785
So sweet.

134
00:07:44,785 --> 00:07:45,426
Okay.

135
00:07:45,905 --> 00:07:47,106
If you have any problems,

136
00:07:47,385 --> 00:07:49,186
just ask me. Don't be shy.

137
00:07:50,866 --> 00:07:52,186
Well, I'll leave.

138
00:07:54,106 --> 00:07:54,626
Bye then.

139
00:08:11,058 --> 00:08:15,127
(Binhai 1st Road)

140
00:08:33,026 --> 00:08:33,745
Hai.

141
00:08:35,066 --> 00:08:35,906
Does it work?

142
00:08:38,266 --> 00:08:39,666
We've been waiting here these days.

143
00:08:40,146 --> 00:08:42,306
A truck comes and you offer help,

144
00:08:43,026 --> 00:08:44,505
and we can earn ten yuan each time.

145
00:08:45,505 --> 00:08:46,266
Just wait.

146
00:08:58,745 --> 00:08:59,266
Come on.

147
00:09:00,105 --> 00:09:00,946
Come on.

148
00:09:01,705 --> 00:09:02,865
Bros, let's go!

149
00:09:03,026 --> 00:09:03,585
Let's go!

150
00:09:07,186 --> 00:09:08,426
What are you all doing?

151
00:09:08,465 --> 00:09:09,426
What are you all doing?

152
00:09:09,446 --> 00:09:09,946
Get down!

153
00:09:09,946 --> 00:09:11,666
Hey, don't get on the truck. Get down!

154
00:09:13,345 --> 00:09:15,906
Think you can push me around
with so many of you?

155
00:09:16,066 --> 00:09:17,426
I have people at the factory too.

156
00:09:17,625 --> 00:09:19,745
Yes, sir. Don't misunderstand.

157
00:09:19,946 --> 00:09:21,266
We're here to move the goods.

158
00:09:21,426 --> 00:09:23,105
See? This is our moving gear.

159
00:09:23,786 --> 00:09:24,306
See?

160
00:09:24,625 --> 00:09:26,786
Sir, we're all locals from Yuehai.

161
00:09:26,946 --> 00:09:29,225
We're honest, hardworking,
and our rates are reasonable.

162
00:09:29,585 --> 00:09:30,625
Just let us help you.

163
00:09:30,786 --> 00:09:31,286
Yes.

164
00:09:32,105 --> 00:09:32,666
How much?

165
00:09:33,066 --> 00:09:33,865
Ten yuan per truck.

166
00:09:35,546 --> 00:09:37,345
Ten? Cheaper.

167
00:09:39,585 --> 00:09:40,465
We can go lower.

168
00:09:47,505 --> 00:09:48,105
Sir,

169
00:09:48,786 --> 00:09:51,985
I'm Zheng Decheng's nephew.

170
00:09:53,946 --> 00:09:56,386
My name's Zheng Zhiqiang,
just call me Qiang.

171
00:10:00,026 --> 00:10:00,705
Qiang.

172
00:10:01,865 --> 00:10:02,705
Ten, right?

173
00:10:03,786 --> 00:10:04,546
Go ahead.

174
00:10:04,705 --> 00:10:05,465
Thanks, sir.

175
00:10:07,266 --> 00:10:08,865
Move it!

176
00:10:09,865 --> 00:10:12,426
Be quick and careful.

177
00:10:19,825 --> 00:10:20,426
Sir.

178
00:10:20,946 --> 00:10:22,546
Know there's a typhoon coming, right?

179
00:10:22,625 --> 00:10:23,186
Yes, I know.

180
00:10:23,426 --> 00:10:24,465
Prepare for it.

181
00:10:24,786 --> 00:10:25,345
Okay.

182
00:10:25,406 --> 00:10:27,026
If you need help, let us know.

183
00:10:27,186 --> 00:10:28,266
Okay, thanks, Ms. Li.

184
00:10:28,426 --> 00:10:29,146
You're welcome.

185
00:10:30,625 --> 00:10:31,306
Sir.

186
00:10:31,406 --> 00:10:31,906
Ma'am.

187
00:10:31,906 --> 00:10:33,146
Know there's a typhoon coming?

188
00:10:33,225 --> 00:10:33,906
Yes, I know.

189
00:10:34,066 --> 00:10:35,625
I heard it could be Force 7 or 8.

190
00:10:35,666 --> 00:10:36,166
Right.

191
00:10:36,186 --> 00:10:37,666
Remember to prepare early.

192
00:10:37,985 --> 00:10:39,906
If you need help, let us know.

193
00:10:39,906 --> 00:10:40,786
Okay, thanks, Ms. Li.

194
00:10:41,026 --> 00:10:41,705
You're welcome.

195
00:10:43,306 --> 00:10:44,306
Yan, going to work?

196
00:10:44,345 --> 00:10:44,985
Ms. Li.

197
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:45,786
I'll help you.

198
00:10:45,985 --> 00:10:47,186
No, it's heavy.

199
00:10:47,306 --> 00:10:47,946
It's fine.

200
00:10:48,105 --> 00:10:48,865
Thanks.

201
00:10:51,865 --> 00:10:53,705
Yan, has Mr. Lin spoken to you?

202
00:10:55,225 --> 00:10:56,266
He has.

203
00:11:00,345 --> 00:11:00,985
Ms. Li,

204
00:11:02,825 --> 00:11:06,906
you told me that he likes me.

205
00:11:07,705 --> 00:11:09,386
Is it really true?

206
00:11:09,705 --> 00:11:10,505
Yes.

207
00:11:10,585 --> 00:11:12,865
He's expressed it to us.
Absolutely genuine.

208
00:11:13,225 --> 00:11:13,825
I promise.

209
00:11:16,505 --> 00:11:17,105
But

210
00:11:19,585 --> 00:11:21,225
he hasn't said anything to me about it.

211
00:11:21,306 --> 00:11:23,386
He's been teaching me
how to build a house.

212
00:11:25,386 --> 00:11:26,985
He's teaching you to build a house?

213
00:11:27,865 --> 00:11:29,426
He is funny.

214
00:11:30,266 --> 00:11:33,186
And he taught me how to use the ink pot.

215
00:11:33,225 --> 00:11:37,266
He said the ink lines must be straight
for the bricks to be laid flat.

216
00:11:38,465 --> 00:11:39,946
Why did he teach you these things?

217
00:11:40,306 --> 00:11:41,666
I'll go talk to him.

218
00:11:41,906 --> 00:11:44,186
Don't, Ms. Li. Please don't.

219
00:11:50,666 --> 00:11:51,166
I...

220
00:11:52,026 --> 00:11:54,505
Actually, I really understand

221
00:11:54,546 --> 00:11:57,745
and I'm very grateful
for your good intentions.

222
00:11:58,426 --> 00:11:59,546
But this matter...

223
00:12:00,666 --> 00:12:02,026
I think maybe...

224
00:12:04,026 --> 00:12:05,625
Just let it be.

225
00:12:06,465 --> 00:12:08,666
Don't force him.
It's really not necessary.

226
00:12:09,386 --> 00:12:11,666
We're not forcing him.
Yan, you've misunderstood.

227
00:12:13,026 --> 00:12:14,906
Maybe everyone
has a different personality,

228
00:12:14,946 --> 00:12:16,426
so their ways of expression differ.

229
00:12:16,705 --> 00:12:19,345
Mr. Lin isn't good with words.
He can't express himself well.

230
00:12:19,985 --> 00:12:22,186
But what he did has already shown

231
00:12:22,225 --> 00:12:24,225
he wants to communicate
and talk with you.

232
00:12:25,046 --> 00:12:25,546
Well...

233
00:12:25,546 --> 00:12:26,186
Ms. Li,

234
00:12:27,426 --> 00:12:30,705
if he doesn't even have the courage
to confess to me,

235
00:12:31,266 --> 00:12:33,266
then why be with him?

236
00:12:33,585 --> 00:12:34,345
Do you agree?

237
00:12:40,426 --> 00:12:41,426
Hai!

238
00:12:42,426 --> 00:12:43,786
Let's go.

239
00:12:44,505 --> 00:12:46,146
What? Can't you see I'm busy?

240
00:12:46,345 --> 00:12:47,225
Zhiqiang.

241
00:12:47,345 --> 00:12:47,865
Granny.

242
00:12:47,946 --> 00:12:49,585
- Granny.
- Granny.

243
00:12:49,745 --> 00:12:52,465
Come and eat Dengzhan cakes.
Come and eat.

244
00:12:52,465 --> 00:12:53,386
- No.
- We've eaten.

245
00:12:53,386 --> 00:12:54,705
We have the baked pancakes.

246
00:12:55,026 --> 00:12:55,546
One for you.

247
00:12:56,465 --> 00:12:57,146
Thank you.

248
00:12:57,186 --> 00:12:58,026
Eat it.

249
00:13:00,625 --> 00:13:01,345
Xiaohai.

250
00:13:02,146 --> 00:13:04,666
You've got both Dengzhan cakes
and baked pancakes.

251
00:13:05,105 --> 00:13:06,345
Where did you get this money?

252
00:13:11,705 --> 00:13:12,266
Granny.

253
00:13:12,745 --> 00:13:15,426
After I get off work at the factory,

254
00:13:15,505 --> 00:13:16,745
I go help others move things.

255
00:13:17,105 --> 00:13:18,745
I can make several yuan each time.

256
00:13:19,225 --> 00:13:20,426
By the end of the day,

257
00:13:20,705 --> 00:13:23,306
I earn more than half a month's wages
at the factory.

258
00:13:23,946 --> 00:13:25,666
Today is Sunday.

259
00:13:26,426 --> 00:13:27,225
So I thought

260
00:13:27,585 --> 00:13:30,146
to take them out to find some gigs.

261
00:13:30,465 --> 00:13:31,146
Have some water.

262
00:13:33,505 --> 00:13:34,426
Moving things?

263
00:13:35,465 --> 00:13:37,906
Granny, moving things pays really well.

264
00:13:38,386 --> 00:13:41,026
And it's hard to get other gigs.

265
00:13:41,046 --> 00:13:41,546
Exactly.

266
00:13:41,546 --> 00:13:42,546
- Indeed.
- Indeed.

267
00:13:42,745 --> 00:13:44,386
That's not what I meant.

268
00:13:44,585 --> 00:13:46,266
I'm just worried about you.

269
00:13:46,825 --> 00:13:50,225
Like Zhiqiang, Xiaohai,
and the rest of you.

270
00:13:50,465 --> 00:13:53,666
You all need to build up your strength.

271
00:13:53,985 --> 00:13:55,865
Don't worry, Granny. We can carry them.

272
00:13:56,546 --> 00:13:58,705
It's not about
whether you can carry them or not.

273
00:13:59,146 --> 00:14:01,345
I'm afraid
you can't fight against the others.

274
00:14:03,426 --> 00:14:03,926
Well...

275
00:14:04,705 --> 00:14:07,426
We just move the goods
and won't fight others, Granny.

276
00:14:08,386 --> 00:14:09,105
See?

277
00:14:10,146 --> 00:14:12,666
What I'm about to say may sound harsh.

278
00:14:13,666 --> 00:14:16,426
Anyone can do manual labor.

279
00:14:17,186 --> 00:14:18,426
But moving things

280
00:14:18,505 --> 00:14:21,426
could lead to turf wars.

281
00:14:22,625 --> 00:14:25,666
Xiaohai, pass me that wooden box.

282
00:14:25,985 --> 00:14:26,786
It's in there.

283
00:14:27,505 --> 00:14:28,825
Over there. In there.

284
00:14:31,625 --> 00:14:34,825
No matter what,
making a living isn't easy for you.

285
00:14:34,985 --> 00:14:36,225
You must be careful.

286
00:14:37,266 --> 00:14:38,745
Give me your gloves.

287
00:14:39,225 --> 00:14:42,026
I'll sew some leather patches
onto them for you,

288
00:14:42,386 --> 00:14:43,426
so you won't get hurt.

289
00:14:44,825 --> 00:14:45,705
Thanks, Granny.

290
00:14:45,745 --> 00:14:46,666
- Thanks.
- Thanks.

291
00:14:46,666 --> 00:14:47,625
You're welcome.

292
00:14:50,546 --> 00:14:51,386
How wonderful.

293
00:14:52,186 --> 00:14:54,505
Granny, you're not eating.

294
00:14:56,745 --> 00:14:57,625
Here, Granny.

295
00:14:57,786 --> 00:14:58,465
Thanks, Granny.

296
00:14:59,946 --> 00:15:00,585
Okay.

297
00:15:00,985 --> 00:15:03,146
You all wait outside for me for a while.

298
00:15:03,345 --> 00:15:03,865
Okay.

299
00:15:04,225 --> 00:15:05,345
- Let's go.
- Everyone out.

300
00:15:05,786 --> 00:15:06,666
Let's go.

301
00:15:06,666 --> 00:15:07,426
Let's go.

302
00:15:08,105 --> 00:15:08,865
Xiaohai.

303
00:15:14,026 --> 00:15:15,146
What is it, Granny?

304
00:15:15,386 --> 00:15:16,026
Xiaohai.

305
00:15:16,666 --> 00:15:18,946
I don't object to you
earning more money.

306
00:15:19,146 --> 00:15:22,345
But you must not quit your factory job.

307
00:15:23,666 --> 00:15:25,946
I just want to make more money

308
00:15:26,225 --> 00:15:27,505
to help with household expenses.

309
00:15:27,546 --> 00:15:29,625
Look how tired
you get pasting these bowls every day.

310
00:15:29,906 --> 00:15:32,306
Besides, if my business takes off later,

311
00:15:32,865 --> 00:15:34,386
I might really not

312
00:15:34,585 --> 00:15:36,186
have time for the factory.

313
00:15:37,546 --> 00:15:39,066
I don't need that much money.

314
00:15:39,505 --> 00:15:41,186
Granny, don't worry.

315
00:15:41,625 --> 00:15:42,786
I've got plenty of strength.

316
00:15:43,105 --> 00:15:44,345
Xiaohai.

317
00:15:44,585 --> 00:15:47,105
At the state-owned factory,
you can learn real skills.

318
00:15:47,666 --> 00:15:51,146
But manual labor wastes your youth.

319
00:15:51,825 --> 00:15:55,426
When you get too old to move things
and have no real skills,

320
00:15:55,625 --> 00:15:58,465
you'll regret it.

321
00:15:58,546 --> 00:15:59,906
I get it, Granny.

322
00:16:00,585 --> 00:16:02,865
You eat first.
Work after you finish eating.

323
00:16:03,026 --> 00:16:03,745
I'll get out.

324
00:16:03,906 --> 00:16:04,546
Mark my words.

325
00:16:04,906 --> 00:16:05,465
Okay.

326
00:16:13,146 --> 00:16:13,666
What's wrong?

327
00:16:13,666 --> 00:16:15,745
Get down!

328
00:16:19,606 --> 00:16:22,533
♪It may sound a little crazy♪

329
00:16:23,384 --> 00:16:25,961
♪And somewhat confusing♪

330
00:16:27,384 --> 00:16:30,434
♪Walking through the night
till morning comes♪

331
00:16:31,336 --> 00:16:34,514
♪Until I reach a beautiful village♪

332
00:16:35,325 --> 00:16:38,424
♪The people here are simple and kind♪

333
00:16:39,544 --> 00:16:41,608
♪Yet I miss my hometown's embrace♪

334
00:16:43,381 --> 00:16:46,610
♪A gentle breeze brushes my face♪

335
00:16:47,460 --> 00:16:50,780
♪Sweeping away unrecoverable days♪

336
00:16:51,434 --> 00:16:55,128
♪Beautiful yet scarred in its own way♪

337
00:16:55,532 --> 00:16:58,154
♪I must summon strength and stay♪

338
00:16:59,443 --> 00:17:02,694
♪Where dreams first began to grow♪

339
00:17:03,491 --> 00:17:06,544
♪I found the girl I cherish so♪

340
00:17:07,302 --> 00:17:10,470
♪I put down my pack and wander no more♪

341
00:17:10,616 --> 00:17:13,971
♪This is my new hometown♪

342
00:17:27,626 --> 00:17:29,705
♪Waves racing♪

343
00:17:30,866 --> 00:17:32,386
♪Waves flowing♪

344
00:17:33,465 --> 00:17:34,985
Stop singing! It sounds awful.

345
00:17:34,985 --> 00:17:36,065
I can't even hear the call.

346
00:17:36,386 --> 00:17:37,225
Ms. Gao's husband.

347
00:17:37,265 --> 00:17:38,346
Ms. Gao's husband, you...

348
00:17:48,946 --> 00:17:50,545
Chunlai, your singing is wonderful.

349
00:17:50,946 --> 00:17:52,065
You flatter wonderfully too.

350
00:17:52,426 --> 00:17:53,745
That ring-ling works great?

351
00:17:54,025 --> 00:17:54,525
Ring-ling?

352
00:17:57,866 --> 00:17:58,826
It works perfectly.

353
00:17:58,985 --> 00:17:59,666
Where's Xuemei?

354
00:17:59,705 --> 00:18:00,205
In there.

355
00:18:08,025 --> 00:18:09,545
You've been counting for ages now.

356
00:18:09,586 --> 00:18:10,985
Have you figured it out yet?

357
00:18:11,866 --> 00:18:13,305
Mom, don't bother me.

358
00:18:13,305 --> 00:18:14,666
I have to start all over again.

359
00:18:15,025 --> 00:18:18,225
See? I told you to get more schooling,
but you refused.

360
00:18:18,545 --> 00:18:20,146
Now you can't even count money properly.

361
00:18:21,225 --> 00:18:22,745
Oh, bring me the contract.

362
00:18:23,065 --> 00:18:24,065
I should double-check it.

363
00:18:24,705 --> 00:18:25,785
Hurry up! Bring it over.

364
00:18:25,785 --> 00:18:27,305
- I have to double-check it.
- But you've checked.

365
00:18:27,465 --> 00:18:29,225
I need to check it again.

366
00:18:29,586 --> 00:18:31,225
That's a 500,000 yuan machine!

367
00:18:31,785 --> 00:18:33,505
Already counted it? Bring it here.

368
00:18:33,785 --> 00:18:35,146
You're always so careless.

369
00:18:35,186 --> 00:18:35,686
I...

370
00:18:36,146 --> 00:18:36,785
Look at you.

371
00:18:36,785 --> 00:18:39,265
Think a 500,000 yuan machine
is a small matter?

372
00:18:43,106 --> 00:18:44,586
Xie, you're here.

373
00:18:45,146 --> 00:18:46,025
Can't I be here?

374
00:18:47,106 --> 00:18:48,426
Of course, you can.

375
00:18:48,646 --> 00:18:49,866
He's here, why not tell me?

376
00:18:49,866 --> 00:18:50,465
Shut it.

377
00:18:57,386 --> 00:18:58,346
It's really 500,000.

378
00:18:59,386 --> 00:19:00,106
Here, let me see.

379
00:19:01,106 --> 00:19:02,305
What?

380
00:19:02,985 --> 00:19:03,745
In your hand.

381
00:19:04,106 --> 00:19:04,626
This?

382
00:19:04,906 --> 00:19:06,025
This is a contract, right?

383
00:19:07,265 --> 00:19:08,426
Is this a contract?

384
00:19:08,906 --> 00:19:09,426
Let me see.

385
00:19:10,866 --> 00:19:11,866
Let me see it.

386
00:19:11,866 --> 00:19:12,626
This is a contract.

387
00:19:13,785 --> 00:19:14,386
Can I see it?

388
00:19:14,985 --> 00:19:15,946
Yes.

389
00:19:20,666 --> 00:19:21,346
Go over there.

390
00:19:22,065 --> 00:19:22,565
Stay away.

391
00:19:23,025 --> 00:19:23,705
Go...

392
00:19:24,146 --> 00:19:25,146
Go over there.

393
00:19:27,985 --> 00:19:29,705
Gao Xuemei, that's you, right?

394
00:19:33,826 --> 00:19:35,146
Ordering one

395
00:19:35,186 --> 00:19:37,705
imported printing machine
for 500,000 yuan.

396
00:19:38,346 --> 00:19:40,106
Dad, not exactly. It costs 498,000 yuan.

397
00:19:40,446 --> 00:19:40,946
And two...

398
00:19:40,946 --> 00:19:42,705
Just shut up!

399
00:19:42,745 --> 00:19:43,505
Do you know it?

400
00:19:44,025 --> 00:19:44,545
No idea.

401
00:19:44,666 --> 00:19:46,225
Then sit down. Answer my questions.

402
00:19:46,666 --> 00:19:47,166
Sit down.

403
00:19:48,906 --> 00:19:49,545
You know that?

404
00:19:50,545 --> 00:19:51,146
Yes.

405
00:19:52,265 --> 00:19:53,265
Then answer my questions.

406
00:19:55,225 --> 00:19:56,785
Do we have many 500,000 yuan?

407
00:20:00,025 --> 00:20:00,946
Just one.

408
00:20:02,186 --> 00:20:02,686
You know it.

409
00:20:03,465 --> 00:20:04,465
So, is this a big deal?

410
00:20:05,106 --> 00:20:05,626
Yes.

411
00:20:06,265 --> 00:20:06,946
Did I ask you?

412
00:20:07,186 --> 00:20:07,866
Do you know it?

413
00:20:08,146 --> 00:20:09,065
I'm asking you.

414
00:20:09,225 --> 00:20:10,985
If not, then don't speak.

415
00:20:11,265 --> 00:20:13,426
If yes, then you're suspicious.

416
00:20:13,866 --> 00:20:14,366
Well...

417
00:20:14,465 --> 00:20:15,826
It is very good, and I...

418
00:20:15,866 --> 00:20:16,626
You stay put.

419
00:20:23,265 --> 00:20:24,186
Why didn't I

420
00:20:25,626 --> 00:20:26,505
know about it?

421
00:20:27,626 --> 00:20:29,065
Tell me why.

422
00:20:30,545 --> 00:20:33,626
I was just about to explain it to you.

423
00:20:34,065 --> 00:20:36,406
I-I'll explain, Xie.

424
00:20:37,265 --> 00:20:38,626
Wait, let go! I...

425
00:20:38,906 --> 00:20:40,386
I need to hold it to explain.

426
00:20:40,745 --> 00:20:43,686
L-Let go, and I'll explain, okay?

427
00:20:43,946 --> 00:20:44,446
You...

428
00:20:47,025 --> 00:20:47,946
Look...

429
00:20:48,505 --> 00:20:49,005
This...

430
00:20:50,065 --> 00:20:50,826
This...

431
00:20:51,186 --> 00:20:51,906
Is it...

432
00:20:52,426 --> 00:20:53,626
At the time...

433
00:20:54,866 --> 00:20:56,906
It was ordered by a Shenzhen factory.

434
00:20:57,346 --> 00:20:59,025
This machine was at sea

435
00:20:59,346 --> 00:21:02,305
for three months.

436
00:21:02,946 --> 00:21:04,426
Then it docked at Shenzhen Port.

437
00:21:04,586 --> 00:21:06,946
But that factory ran out of funds.

438
00:21:07,465 --> 00:21:09,346
They had to sell it
at a 30 percent discount.

439
00:21:09,505 --> 00:21:11,186
Otherwise, we couldn't have afforded it.

440
00:21:12,985 --> 00:21:14,346
So we got a good bargain!

441
00:21:14,545 --> 00:21:15,305
Exactly!

442
00:21:15,545 --> 00:21:16,346
I get it now, right?

443
00:21:16,586 --> 00:21:17,086
Yes.

444
00:21:17,146 --> 00:21:20,285
So this machine was at sea...

445
00:21:20,946 --> 00:21:22,065
Right? It was at sea,

446
00:21:22,926 --> 00:21:23,426
right?

447
00:21:23,426 --> 00:21:23,985
No need.

448
00:21:23,985 --> 00:21:27,186
And it finally reached us.

449
00:21:27,386 --> 00:21:28,426
Such a bargain, right?

450
00:21:28,465 --> 00:21:29,705
Go sit down and stay put.

451
00:21:31,586 --> 00:21:33,426
I really got a great bargain.

452
00:21:33,426 --> 00:21:34,785
I am so ignorant.

453
00:21:34,785 --> 00:21:36,505
Right, Gao Xuemei?

454
00:21:36,505 --> 00:21:37,426
Is that what I asked?

455
00:21:37,985 --> 00:21:39,106
Is that?

456
00:21:39,505 --> 00:21:40,505
Is that what I asked?

457
00:21:40,525 --> 00:21:41,025
What was it?

458
00:21:41,025 --> 00:21:41,906
Is that what I asked?

459
00:21:42,025 --> 00:21:43,065
Is that what I asked?

460
00:21:44,426 --> 00:21:45,265
I... Well...

461
00:21:45,465 --> 00:21:48,346
Why didn't you tell me
about such a big deal?

462
00:21:49,146 --> 00:21:49,826
Right?

463
00:21:50,346 --> 00:21:51,545
So you should...

464
00:21:51,586 --> 00:21:52,626
Why?

465
00:21:53,386 --> 00:21:54,146
What are you doing?

466
00:21:54,146 --> 00:21:55,705
Don't, Xie.

467
00:21:55,965 --> 00:21:56,465
Wait...

468
00:21:56,465 --> 00:21:57,065
Go away.

469
00:21:57,065 --> 00:21:57,745
- Yes.
- Go back.

470
00:21:57,745 --> 00:21:58,906
- Go stay put.
- Go away.

471
00:22:00,545 --> 00:22:01,386
I'm not...

472
00:22:03,866 --> 00:22:05,346
- Wait, Xie, listen.
- What are you doing?

473
00:22:05,346 --> 00:22:06,386
I need to explain.

474
00:22:06,386 --> 00:22:07,065
Explain? Go on.

475
00:22:07,065 --> 00:22:08,505
I've been listening.

476
00:22:08,705 --> 00:22:09,205
Explain it.

477
00:22:09,305 --> 00:22:09,985
Put it down now.

478
00:22:09,985 --> 00:22:10,586
Where?

479
00:22:10,705 --> 00:22:11,346
Can it even fit?

480
00:22:11,346 --> 00:22:11,906
Put it here.

481
00:22:11,906 --> 00:22:12,406
It'll fit?

482
00:22:12,426 --> 00:22:13,065
It fits.

483
00:22:13,586 --> 00:22:14,906
Put it down.

484
00:22:15,146 --> 00:22:16,186
I'm letting go.

485
00:22:16,465 --> 00:22:17,146
You let go.

486
00:22:17,305 --> 00:22:18,146
Let go.

487
00:22:18,626 --> 00:22:19,305
You let go.

488
00:22:19,305 --> 00:22:19,985
I-I let go.

489
00:22:20,346 --> 00:22:21,106
You let go.

490
00:22:21,106 --> 00:22:21,826
I'll let go.

491
00:22:21,985 --> 00:22:22,485
You let go.

492
00:22:22,586 --> 00:22:23,086
I...

493
00:22:23,186 --> 00:22:24,545
Your hand is on top.

494
00:22:24,545 --> 00:22:25,265
Let go together.

495
00:22:25,305 --> 00:22:26,265
Okay, letting go!

496
00:22:26,785 --> 00:22:27,285
Okay.

497
00:22:30,025 --> 00:22:30,525
Xie.

498
00:22:32,166 --> 00:22:32,666
Look.

499
00:22:32,666 --> 00:22:33,666
My shoe came off.

500
00:22:33,906 --> 00:22:34,705
Don't.

501
00:22:35,386 --> 00:22:36,586
Don't. Put it down!

502
00:22:36,666 --> 00:22:37,346
What am I doing?

503
00:22:37,346 --> 00:22:37,866
You tell me.

504
00:22:37,866 --> 00:22:38,785
Don't touch it.

505
00:22:39,386 --> 00:22:40,866
What are you doing? Give it to me!

506
00:22:41,225 --> 00:22:41,745
Put it down!

507
00:22:42,025 --> 00:22:42,545
Give me!

508
00:22:42,946 --> 00:22:43,666
Give me!

509
00:22:44,186 --> 00:22:45,146
Stop it!

510
00:22:45,225 --> 00:22:46,426
Give me! You!

511
00:22:57,705 --> 00:22:59,545
Move!

512
00:22:59,626 --> 00:23:00,346
Move!

513
00:23:02,386 --> 00:23:02,985
Go, go!

514
00:23:03,426 --> 00:23:04,025
Clear out!

515
00:23:08,186 --> 00:23:09,225
Calm down, Xie.

516
00:23:10,785 --> 00:23:11,672
It's bleeding.

517
00:23:12,146 --> 00:23:12,705
Shut up!

518
00:23:14,225 --> 00:23:16,225
Well, you got injured?

519
00:23:18,065 --> 00:23:18,906
Sorry, sorry.

520
00:23:18,946 --> 00:23:19,465
I'm sorry.

521
00:23:19,705 --> 00:23:20,785
I didn't mean to, Xie.

522
00:23:20,785 --> 00:23:21,626
You injured me?

523
00:23:21,985 --> 00:23:23,826
No! This is just a scratch.

524
00:23:23,906 --> 00:23:26,106
You injured me for this stupid machine?

525
00:23:26,186 --> 00:23:26,906
I didn't.

526
00:23:26,946 --> 00:23:27,626
Clawed me?

527
00:23:27,705 --> 00:23:29,586
This is a scratch! And this is a touch!

528
00:23:31,586 --> 00:23:32,312
Bleeding again.

529
00:23:33,946 --> 00:23:35,065
S-Sorry.

530
00:23:35,586 --> 00:23:36,426
S-Sorry.

531
00:23:37,106 --> 00:23:37,606
Okay.

532
00:23:42,514 --> 00:23:43,852
(Factory Director's Office)

533
00:23:47,305 --> 00:23:47,946
Got it?

534
00:23:49,225 --> 00:23:49,826
Got it.

535
00:23:50,265 --> 00:23:50,866
Repeat it.

536
00:23:51,465 --> 00:23:52,386
You, repeat it.

537
00:23:52,785 --> 00:23:53,666
To return the machine.

538
00:23:59,386 --> 00:23:59,985
Got it?

539
00:24:00,225 --> 00:24:00,866
Got it.

540
00:24:06,866 --> 00:24:07,545
Take care.

541
00:24:08,882 --> 00:24:12,235
(Actively Promote
the Five Do's and Four Upliftings)

542
00:24:14,106 --> 00:24:14,666
Take it easy.

543
00:24:14,785 --> 00:24:16,985
Hai, Granny was right about this.

544
00:24:17,265 --> 00:24:18,505
There is a turf war.

545
00:24:19,465 --> 00:24:21,025
Hai, what should we do?

546
00:24:21,426 --> 00:24:23,065
Just deal with it.

547
00:24:24,305 --> 00:24:25,305
They started it.

548
00:24:25,586 --> 00:24:26,545
We have to fight back.

549
00:24:27,265 --> 00:24:27,765
Qiang.

550
00:24:28,505 --> 00:24:30,265
See that guy in black?

551
00:24:30,985 --> 00:24:34,265
That's Wang Wu.
I fought him before, he fights dirty.

552
00:24:34,705 --> 00:24:35,265
Be careful.

553
00:24:38,146 --> 00:24:38,646
Hai.

554
00:24:41,186 --> 00:24:42,146
Let's help him move it.

555
00:24:42,225 --> 00:24:43,545
Then we'll charge later.

556
00:24:47,225 --> 00:24:47,725
Let's go.

557
00:24:47,906 --> 00:24:48,406
- Let's go.
- Let's go

558
00:24:51,745 --> 00:24:52,245
Wu.

559
00:24:55,705 --> 00:24:56,346
Who are you?

560
00:24:56,705 --> 00:24:57,985
Wu, it's me, Xiaohai.

561
00:24:58,705 --> 00:24:59,545
These are my buddies.

562
00:25:00,505 --> 00:25:01,186
What do you mean?

563
00:25:01,626 --> 00:25:04,025
You've got so much to move.
We're here to help you.

564
00:25:04,866 --> 00:25:06,680
What are you waiting for? Help Wu!

565
00:25:06,680 --> 00:25:07,505
Come on, help Wu.

566
00:25:07,545 --> 00:25:08,225
Let's help Wu!

567
00:25:08,326 --> 00:25:08,826
Come on.

568
00:25:08,826 --> 00:25:09,545
You take a break.

569
00:25:11,545 --> 00:25:12,386
Easy, easy.

570
00:25:14,826 --> 00:25:15,465
That room?

571
00:25:19,225 --> 00:25:20,305
Done already?

572
00:25:21,586 --> 00:25:22,705
